latestPosts.caption:
If banana bread could melt into a cup this would be it.
Toasty, nutty, subtly sweet with a hint of spice!  Hojicha from @mezamematchaclub 

So I started by making a quick banana syrup using ripe bananas, some jaggery (you can use brown sugar too), and cinnamon. Cooked it all on low till it turned into this thick, caramel-y sauce. Blended it smooth so there are no chunks.

I mixed that with oat milk super simple.
And for the hojicha, I used 3 grams to get a stronger, deeper flavor. It’s roasted green tea, so it’s not grassy like matcha it’s more chocolatey, warm, and kind of bakery-like. You’ll love it even if you don’t usually like matcha.

There’s no actual banana bread in here, but somehow the whole thing just tastes like a cozy baked treat in a glass. So good.

Would you try this?

How does spirulina taste? Just a pinch has an ocean-y, seaweed-like flavor but blend it into smoothies or protein bowls with fruits, and you won’t even notice it.
With benefits this big, don’t overthink it  just add it in and let it work its magic!
What is seed cycling blend?
It’s packed with pumpkin & flax seeds with a boost of hemp, moringa & shatavari to support estrogen in the first half of your cycle.
seeds to naturally support hormone balance and keep the cycle in sync.
A small addition, but it goes a long way in nurturing your body from within.

So basically, This is the only yogurt bowl you need to start your day right packed with protein, loaded with antioxidants from @gunambeauty blue spirulina and the calm energy of matcha.
Added my fav seed cycling blend from @samah_in , Greek yogurt (17 grams protein )from @epigamia.official , topped with pecan granola and mixed seeds  bananas and blueberries!!!and that’s a power-packed breakfast right there. Flavour and nourishment
